		<title>LG to Bring AirPlay to Hotel Room TVs Later This Year</title>
		<link>https://www.macrumors.com/2023/06/22/lg-airplay-hotel-room-tvs/</link>
		<comments>https://forums.macrumors.com/threads/lg-to-bring-airplay-to-hotel-room-tvs-later-this-year.2393888/</comments>
		<pubDate>Thu, 22 Jun 2023 16:31:00 PDT</pubDate>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.macrumors.com/2023/06/22/lg-airplay-hotel-room-tvs/</guid>
		<dc:creator>Juli Clover</dc:creator>
		<category>AirPlay</category>
		<category>LG</category>
		

		<description><![CDATA[LG Electronics will be one of the first TV manufacturers to support Apple's <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/guide/airplay/">AirPlay</a> expansion, which will see Apple bringing easy access &zwnj;AirPlay&zwnj; to hotel room TVs.<br/>
<br/>
<img src="https://images.macrumors.com/article-new/2023/06/airplay-hotels.jpg" alt="" width="1600" height="894" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-898340" /><br/>
In a <a href="https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/lg-first-to-bring-apple-airplay-to-hotel-room-tvs-301858034.html">press release</a> (via <em><a href="https://www.zdnet.com/article/apple-and-lg-partner-up-to-fix-the-biggest-problem-with-hotel-tvs/">ZDNET</a></em>), LG said that later this year, it will introduce LG Pro:Centric Smart Hotel TVs that include built-in &zwnj;AirPlay&zwnj; technology.<br/>
<br/>
"This is a major advancement for in-room entertainment in the travel and hospitality industry, and underscores how closely we are listening to the needs of consumers who increasingly demand simple access to their personal media options on the biggest screen, wherever they are," said LG Business Solutions hospitality vice president Michael Kosla. "Hotels that offer this feature will have an immediate leg up with travelers who use Apple devices, boosting guest satisfaction while providing real differentiation from local competition."<br/>
<br/>
LG worked with Apple to make an easy-to-use &zwnj;AirPlay&zwnj; solution. <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/guide/iphone/">iPhone</a> users will be able to scan a QR code to access &zwnj;AirPlay&zwnj;, allowing them to to securely play content from an &zwnj;iPhone&zwnj; or <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/ipad/">iPad</a> to a hotel room TV with no need for extra equipment. LG says &zwnj;AirPlay&zwnj; will work on the TVs it is releasing this year as well as "recent year's models."<br/>
<br/>
Apple <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/2023/06/05/apple-ios-17-new-intelligent-airplay/">at WWDC said</a> that it is partnering with select hotels to bring &zwnj;AirPlay&zwnj; to supported television sets. IHG Hotels &amp; Resorts, which operates 6,000 locations worldwide, will be one of the first companies to support &zwnj;AirPlay&zwnj; in its hotels.<div class="linkback">Tags: <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/guide/airplay/">AirPlay</a>, <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/guide/lg/">LG</a></div><br/>This article, &quot;<a href="https://www.macrumors.com/2023/06/22/lg-airplay-hotel-room-tvs/">LG to Bring AirPlay to Hotel Room TVs Later This Year</a>&quot; first appeared on <a href="https://www.macrumors.com">MacRumors.com</a><br/><br/><a href="https://forums.macrumors.com/threads/lg-to-bring-airplay-to-hotel-room-tvs-later-this-year.2393888/">Discuss this article</a> in our forums<br/><br/>]]></description>
