		<title>Here Are All the &#039;Environments&#039; You Can Experience in visionOS</title>
		<link>https://www.macrumors.com/2023/06/21/visionos-environments/</link>
		<comments>https://forums.macrumors.com/threads/here-are-all-the-environments-you-can-experience-in-visionos.2393782/</comments>
		<pubDate>Wed, 21 Jun 2023 16:00:46 PDT</pubDate>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.macrumors.com/2023/06/21/visionos-environments/</guid>
		<dc:creator>Juli Clover</dc:creator>
		<category>visionOS</category>
		

		<description><![CDATA[With the Vision Pro headset, there is an option to activate an Environment that allows you to shut out the world around you. While Apple has mentioned Mount Hood as an Environment you can visit and use as a backdrop, there are several others.<br/>
<br/>
<img src="https://images.macrumors.com/article-new/2023/06/vision-pro-environments.jpg" alt="" width="2290" height="1288" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-901362" /><br/>
Apple today released the first version of <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/visionos/">visionOS</a>, which can be experienced using the latest Xcode beta, and the &zwnj;visionOS&zwnj; update has given us some insight into new &zwnj;visionOS&zwnj; features. Here are the available environments right now:<br/>
<ul><br/>
 	<li>Haleakalā</li><br/>
 	<li>Yosemite</li><br/>
 	<li>Sky</li><br/>
 	<li>Joshua Tree</li><br/>
 	<li>Lake Vrangla</li><br/>
 	<li>Mount Hood</li><br/>
 	<li>The Moon</li><br/>
 	<li>Beach</li><br/>
 	<li>White Sands</li><br/>
 	<li>Winter Light</li><br/>
 	<li>Fall Light</li><br/>
 	<li>Summer Light</li><br/>
 	<li>Spring Light</li><br/>
</ul><br/>
Vision Pro users will be able to enter a virtual environment by turning the Digital Crown to shut out the real world. Environments can be used as a background for watching movies, using apps, making calls, and more.<br/>
<br/>
