		<description><![CDATA[Apple today released a second Studio Display 17 firmware beta, with the update coming two weeks after the release of the first beta.<br/>
<br/>
<img src="https://images.macrumors.com/article-new/2022/03/apple-studio-display-blue.jpg" alt="" width="2250" height="1266" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-839183" /><br/>
All Studio Display models are able to receive over-the-air firmware updates, but this firmware update is limited to Macs that are running the new <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/macos-sonoma/">macOS Sonoma</a> operating system at the current time. Studio Display owners running &zwnj;macOS Sonoma&zwnj; can go to System Settings > Software Update to install the firmware.<br/>
